(power_switching, time).explanation: Higher switching power consumption can lead to thermal throttling and power management interventions that reduce processor frequency, thereby increasing execution time;

(power_switching, power_clock).explanation: Switching power and clock power are independent components of total power consumption, with switching power arising from logic state changes and clock power from clock distribution networks;

(power_switching, area_net_area).explanation: Switching power is a dynamic electrical property while net area is a static physical layout characteristic, with no direct causal relationship between power consumption and interconnect area;
